BUG: Right-click context menu on TFrameAnimationWindow positions incorrectly.

The menu appears offset from the mouse click — the further from origin (0,0), the larger the offset. Classic coordinate double-conversion.

Current code in app/test_pattern_app.cpp, inside TFrameAnimationWindow::handleEvent:

            TPoint deskPt;
            deskPt.x = origin.x + event.mouse.where.x;
            deskPt.y = origin.y + event.mouse.where.y;
            TRect deskExt = owner->getExtent();
            TRect r(deskPt.x, deskPt.y, deskExt.b.x, deskExt.b.y);
            TMenuBox* box = new TMenuBox(r, popup, nullptr);
            ushort cmd = owner->execView(box);

The menu is executed via owner->execView(box) where owner is the TDeskTop.

event.mouse.where in TView::handleEvent is documented as local to the view.
TWindow is a TGroup — events dispatched to child views get coords mapped by the group.
But TFrameAnimationWindow::handleEvent catches the event before child dispatch.

The TMenuBox is inserted into the owner (desktop) coordinate space via execView.

Attempts so far:
1. makeGlobal(event.mouse.where) then owner->makeLocal() — still offset
2. origin.x + event.mouse.where.x — still offset

Fix the coordinate conversion so the TMenuBox appears at the mouse cursor position. Only edit app/test_pattern_app.cpp.
